DESCRIPTION:<p>Here’s a link to the April second Saturday ride: <a href="ht
 tps://ridewithgps.com/routes/54531276" target="_blank">https://ridewithgps.
 com/<wbr />routes/54531276</a><u></u><u></u></p><p>The plan is to start fro
 m Sutter High School at 9:30 a.m.\, bike 39 miles around the Sutter Buttes\
 , and then\, if you have time\, have a late lunch in the town of Sutter at 
 Sutter Cut Pizzeria\, or maybe French Whisk or Taco Time. Because food is o
 nly available at the end of the ride\, you should carry snacks.<u></u><u></
 u></p><p>More details below. Please let me know if you need additional info
 rmation.<u></u><u></u></p><p>Thanks\,<u></u><u></u></p><p>-Anne<u></u><u></
 u></p><p>(916) 206-2922<u></u><u></u></p><ul><li>Date: Second Saturday – Ap
 ril 11\, 2026<u></u><u></u></li><li>Start time: <b>9:30</b> a.m.<u></u><u><
 /u></li><li>Start location: Town of Sutter: parking lot of the Sutter Union
  High School at 2665 Acacia Ave\, Sutter\, CA 95982.<u></u><u></u></li><li>
 Distance: 39 miles\, ~500 feet of climbing<u></u><u></u></li><li>Contact: A
 nne Huber\; <a href="mailto:anneh@dcn.org" target="_blank">anneh@dcn.org</a
 >\; 916-206-2922<u></u><u></u></li><li>Services (Food\, water\, bathrooms):
  No food until end of ride\, so bring a snack. Also\, no real bathrooms alo
 ng the route.<u></u><u></u></li><li>No need to RSVP<u></u><u></u></li><li>R
 ain cancellation or postponement: communicated via the listserv.<u></u><u><
 /u></li><li>Pace: 14 - 17 mph with regroups. The speed is meant to be an in
 dicator of speed on flat terrain with no wind. People can go faster if they
  want as long as they are willing to regroup. There might be some stopping 
 for scenery.<u></u><u></u></li><li>Route: <a href="https://ridewithgps.com/
 routes/54531276" target="_blank">https://ridewithgps.com/<wbr />routes/5453
 1276</a><u></u><u></u></li></ul><p><u></u> <u></u></p><ul><li>For general i
 nformation about the second Saturday ride and bicycling with the Davis Bike
  Club\, please see: <a href="https://davisbikeclub.org/2nd-sat-explorer-rid
 e/" target="_blank">https://davisbikeclub.org/2nd-<wbr />sat-explorer-ride/
 </a><u></u><u></u></li></ul><p>This link includes the following: “Cycling h
 as inherent risks. Any cyclist taking part in a DBC ride releases DBC from 
 any liability. Guests are welcome to ride with DBC for one ride\; for subse
 quent rides\, you must be a member of the Club. By riding with a DBC group 
 ride you acknowledge that you have read and understand this. Helmets are re
 quired on all rides.”</p>
